##################################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");

##################################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");

$r = random(11,35,1);
$b = 1 + $r/100;
$decimal = $r/100;

$answer = Real("$b");


##################################
#  Main Text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

What is the growth/decay factor per decade for a city whose population grows by $r$PERCENT per decade?
$PAR
The growth/decay factor is \(b = \)
\{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

##################################
#  Answer Evaluation

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS($answer->cmp() );


##################################
#  Solution


Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR

The decennial growth factor (growth factor per 10 years) is \(1 + r\) per decade.  We have \(r = $r\)${PERCENT} \(= $decimal\), so the growth factor \(b =  $b\).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

;
ENDDOCUMENT();
